data.title: The Marriage of Princess Helena, 5 July 1866
data.meta_description: The marriage of Princess Helena with Prince Christian of Schleswig-Holstein took place in the Private Chapel at Windsor Castle. The Archbishop of Canterbury, Charles Longley, performed the ceremony. Queen Victoria can be seen standing just behind the bridal couple and in the gallery above are the choir and a number of guests.
